snippet.textDisplay: This whole connecting the Venomverse to the Spider-Man MCU films, but not the overall MCU, ...is weird.  I don’t hate it though.  They’re gonna have to recognize the snap/blip somehow though, right?  I mean you have to, with just like a throwaway line like “things are finally getting back to normal” or something small like that.    ....  The whole snap/5 years later thing ... might have been a mistake.  I’m worried that all these movies are gonna start ignoring it to better their own stories, but in doing that, it makes the whole thing not make sense, since things for everyone in the universe would be SO different.  I mean half of all life was snapped back into existence on top of whatever the other half had going on, that’s gonna heavily affect everyone’s lives in every country, not to mention every other planet.  To make it truly work, they’re gonna have to have a lot of new stories, structures, heroes’ origins, and villains’ origins stem from everybody coming back.
